The White House Press Secretary released a statement regarding three bills: H.R. 533, H.R. 615, and H.R. 893. H.R. 533 involves revoking the charter of incorporation of the Miami Tribe of Oklahoma, at the tribe's request. H.R. 615, known as the "Department of Homeland Security Interoperable Communications Act," expands the responsibilities of the Under Secretary for Management of the Department of Homeland Security to include managing and administering policies and directives to achieve and maintain interoperable communications among the department's components. Lastly, H.R. 893, called the "Boys Town Centennial Commemorative Coin Act," requires the Department of the Treasury to create and issue coins in celebration of the centennial of the founding of Father Flanagan's Boys Town.